sections.body:
Every application made under this Act—
shall be in such manner as may be prescribed;
shall be supported by such evidence of the statements made therein as may be prescribed;
shall be verified by affidavit or a declaration made before a magistrate or commissioner for oaths; and
shall be accompanied by such fee as may be prescribed.

(1)
The Citizenship of Zambia Act, Chapter 121 of the Revised Edition, is hereby repealed.
The Citizenship of Zambia Act, Chapter 121 of the Revised Edition, is hereby repealed.
(2)
Notwithstanding the repeal of the said Act—
(a)
any regulations made under that Act;
(b)
any certificates, orders and acts, granted, made or done, as the case may be, under that Act;
having force and effect, or in operation, as the case may be, immediately before the commencement of this Act shall, in so far as they are not inconsistent with this Act, be deemed to have been made, granted or done, as the case may be, under this Act.
